parameters:
Former Imperial Dark Agent Luid: 'Amina, tell me! When was
the last time I was so surprised that they came to visit?'

Maid Amina: Since it was decided to present the mansion to
the king, it has been effectively confiscated... Well, at
least I still have my life, so it could be worse.

Maid Amina: Thanks to all of you, both Luid and I are alive.
I am especially grateful for having been released from
Caron's curse.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Luid: There are still parts that
I haven't fully digested... but I think on the day my father
died, my mother also passed away.

\CL 【The Aftermath of Former Imperial Dark Agent Luid】Luid
provides all the information about the Dark Agency during
Queen Caron's reign to King Lex. In exchange for offering
numerous lands and information that he possessed, he
receives a pardon.

\CL For a while, Luid continued his espionage activities as
King Lex's shadow, but eventually retired. He returned to
the mansion where he once lived with Caron and married
Amina.

\CL He was monitored by the Dark Agency throughout his life,
but he managed to have children on the sly.

\CL 【The Aftermath of Maid Amina】Like Luid, she actively
cooperated with King Lex and received a pardon. She
continued to be targeted by the dark agents during Caron's
reign and fought alongside Luid.

\CL She initially opposed returning to the former mansion,
but eventually complied. Luid's proposal was I want you to
stay by my side from now on.

\CL She kept those words for her entire life, and three days
after Luid's death, she also passed away in this world.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Clea (We haven't talked yet, have we?)

3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Clea: Our relationship has changed in various ways from our
first meeting to reclaiming the throne, but I'm happy that
we can talk again with smiles on our faces.

Former Imperial Dark Operative, Luid: I really have to thank
you, not just for me... but for risking your life for all of
us.

Former Imperial Dark Operative, Luid: I don't think I'll
have a stable residence for a while, but when I have a
proper place to live, come visit me as a friend.

Mage Relm: I absolutely won't forgive anyone who cooperated
with Elatoma.

Former Imperial Dark Operative, Luid: It's just an excuse to
say it was just a job... From now on, I should be facing
days of atonement and retribution.

Mage Relm: Please take care of Amina-san and make sure you
don't mix up the order of what is truly important.
Thief Nora: You absolutely must not make Amina-san cry!

Former Imperial Dark Operative, Luid: I promise that I will
never do anything to make Amina cry.

Thief Nora: Then I can rest easy! Please make sure the two
of you become happy together!

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, just like my senior in the Dark
Operatives, many pursuers will come after you from now on.

Former Imperial Dark Operative, Luid: Ahaha, I appreciate
the advice from my senior. I will survive just like you,
together with Amina.

Priestess Sophia: That's a good thing. Please make sure to
invite me as a priestess to the wedding, okay?

Clea: There was talk about breaking Luid's curse, but it was
not us who did it, but Amina's dedication.

Maid Amina: If you say so... Well, the fact remains that she
fought with her life on the line.

Maid Amina: From now on, we will be fighting against the
remnants of the dark faction. It may not be easy right away,
but let's take our time and talk later.

Mage Relm: I was surprised when I found out about Luid-san
and Amina-san's true identities.

Maid Amina: I apologize for pretending to hide my true
identity. Thanks to all of you, I no longer need to wear a
false mask.

Mage Relm: I intend to become an Archmage. If you ever find
yourself in trouble, please come to the neutral Magic
Academy!
Thief Nora: Please keep a close eye on Luid-san!

Maid Amina: Of course, there has never been a master who can
rival a maid since ancient times.

Thief Nora: Well then, you can rest assured! If you ever
find yourself in trouble, please rely on the Emma Mercenary
Corps!

Priestess Sophia: Our meeting, and the current situation...
How much of life is predetermined, and how much is just a
coincidence?

Maid Amina: I have learned from all of you to overcome any
pain and despair and seize the inevitability that I desire,
haven't I?

Priestess Sophia: Then please grasp the inevitability
without giving up. Even if we hunt down the remnants, the
assassins will surely come after us.

Former Imperial Dark Division member, Lloyd: 'Actually, we
have a special guest! It's thanks to the Supreme God Sol
that you all came today!'

Former General Atu: Hahaha, I'm delighted to see you all
here! I never expected to meet you!

Former General Atu: Continuing from that night might be
interesting!
Clea: General Atu, you're alive... What on earth...?

Thief Nora: That scent of a child's room...! The strong
scent must be General Atu!

Former General Atu: The mirror in that room is a hidden
staircase leading to the first floor. There are similar
tricks everywhere, so escaping should be easy!

Priestess Sophia: The wounds were so severe that healing
couldn't keep up. Is there some kind of secret behind
them...?

Former General Atu: Hahaha, it's all about meat, cheese, and
training! Think about it carefully, do you really think I
would die from just a little injury?

Mage Relm: I wonder what it is, this abnormal level of
persuasiveness...
Clea: What about the boy next to you...?
Former General Atu: He is the second prince.

Former General Atu: Sibling killing over the throne may be a
tradition in the empire, but I cannot allow it without a
fair and honorable fight.

Former General Atu: This child is just a victim. No matter
what happens, I intend to protect this child until the end.
Former General Atu: Will you stop me, Sophia?

Priestess Sophia: That is something decided by King Rex, and
I have decided to live as a priestess.

Former General Atu: That's right! That's exactly what makes
us comrades who fought through that insane night!

Former General Atu: That's right! That's exactly what makes
us comrades who fought through that insane night!

\CL 【Former General Atu's Whereabouts】After being
temporarily sheltered by Luid, he disappears out of concern
for Luid's safety. While evading King Rex's pursuers
repeatedly, he wanders throughout the empire.

\CL During the Third Tarasa War, he/she spontaneously joins
the battle as an unknown warrior. Their true identity is
exposed due to their remarkable achievements, but they go
missing in the midst of the battlefield.

\CL Due to their recklessness and charm, they will be talked
about as a hero of the people for a long time.

\CL 【The Aftermath of the Second Prince Catala】After losing
his beloved mother Caron, he continues his escape in
despair. However, he is trained both mentally and physically
under Atu's guidance and faces his destiny head-on.

\CL They abandoned their original name and eventually began
to travel across battlefields with Atu. They participated in
the Third Tarasa War and ran across the battlefield as a
brave and fearless warrior.

\CL His name was erased by King Rex and completely erased
from the history of the empire.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Clea: I'm glad to be able to see you alive again. I've been
in your care since I was just starting out, General Atu.

General Atu: It's deeply moving to see you now, looking like
a completely different person from when you were just a
rookie.

Former General Atu: Even I, who was called the strongest in
the empire, feared Rex. Don't get used to fighting, because
the battlefield is always unpredictable.

Mage Relm: Thank you for saving us. Because you saved us,
you ended up getting injured as well...

Former General Atu: Hahaha, you're too kind to be a warrior.
You suit being a mage! Keep working hard, little one!

Mage Relm: Kids are unnecessary! Well, it's natural for me
since I aim to become an Archmage!

Thief Nora: Thank you very much for helping me in various
ways during the bandit subjugation in Camps!

Former General Atu: Hahaha, don't worry about it! The battle
against the leader of the Emma Bandit Gang was magnificent!

Thief Nora: The captain praised me too! I'll become even
stronger for the sake of my comrades from now on!

Priestess Sophia: Do you not consider the possibility of
reconciliation with King Rex?

Former General Atu: I don't acknowledge the monster within
him, but the only thing I do acknowledge is his unwavering
commitment to his words and actions.

Priestess Sophia: We will execute Queen Caron and General
Atu... Yes, it is impossible to reconcile with King Rex,
isn't it?

Second Prince Catala: Who might you all be? Could you
possibly be friends of my mother?
